```", "new_string": "# Plan: Fix Promotion Multi-Line Reuse Bug in checkout()

## Context

`checkout()` in `promotions.service.ts` uses `appliedPromotionIds.has(promo.id)` (line 176) to skip any promotion already applied to a previous line item. This means once promotion A is applied to line 1, it cannot apply to line 2 even if line 2 is independently eligible. This violates the requirement that a promotion may apply to multiple lines unless explicitly excluded via `PromotionExclusion`.

The `appliedPromotionIds` Set must be **kept** — it is still needed to enforce order-level mutual exclusions (if promo A excludes promo B, applying A to any line blocks B on all subsequent lines). The fix is simply to stop using the set as a "used" guard and use it only as an "exclusion context" guard.

## Root Cause (single line)

**`backend/src/modules/promotions/promotions.service.ts` line 176:**
```typescript
if (appliedPromotionIds.has(promo.id)) continue;  // ← remove this line
```

The two checks that follow (lines 179–186) — `conflictsWithApplied` and `alreadyAppliedExcludesThis` — are correct and must be preserved unchanged.

## Changes

### 1. `backend/src/modules/promotions/promotions.service.ts`

Remove line 176 entirely:
```typescript
// DELETE this line:
if (appliedPromotionIds.has(promo.id)) continue;
```

No other changes to the service. The `appliedPromotionIds` declaration (line 163) and its `add()` call (line 208) remain — they are still required for the exclusion checks on lines 180 and 182–185.

### 2. `unit_tests/promotions.test.ts`

**A. Fix `resolveBestPromotion` helper** (line 67) — remove the matching skip-if-applied guard so the helper mirrors the corrected service:
```typescript
// DELETE this line from resolveBestPromotion:
if (appliedIds.has(promo.id)) continue;
```

**B. Update "skips excluded promotions" test** — after the fix, promo 1 (already applied) CAN be re-applied to a new line. Promo 2 (which excludes promo 1) is still correctly blocked. Change:
```typescript
// OLD:
expect(best).toBeNull();
// NEW:
expect(best?.id).toBe(1); // promo 1 re-applies; promo 2 is blocked by its own exclusion of promo 1
```

**C. Update "applies mutual exclusion correctly" test** — after the fix, promo 1 (already applied, excludes promo 2) can be re-applied. Promo 2 is still blocked (alreadyAppliedExcludesThis). Change:
```typescript
// OLD:
expect(best).toBeNull();
// NEW:
expect(best?.id).toBe(1); // promo 1 re-applies; promo 2 blocked because promo 1 (applied) excludes it
```

**D. Add new test — same promotion applies to multiple lines** (in "Conflict Resolution" describe):
```typescript
it('allows the same promotion to apply to multiple lines', () => {
  const promos: MockPromotion[] = [
    { id: 1, priority: 5, discountType: 'PERCENTAGE', discountValue: 10, exclusionsFrom: [] },
  ];
  // Line 1 — promo 1 is selected
  const line1Best = resolveBestPromotion(promos, 100, 1, new Set());
  expect(line1Best?.id).toBe(1);

  // Line 2 — same promo, no exclusion conflict, should still be selected
  const appliedAfterLine1 = new Set<number>([1]);
  const line2Best = resolveBestPromotion(promos, 100, 1, appliedAfterLine1);
  expect(line2Best?.id).toBe(1);
});
```

**E. Add new test — exclusion still blocks across lines** (in "Conflict Resolution" describe):
```typescript
it('exclusion prevents a conflicting promotion on subsequent lines', () => {
  // Promo 1 explicitly excludes promo 2
  const promos: MockPromotion[] = [
    { id: 1, priority: 5, discountType: 'PERCENTAGE', discountValue: 10, exclusionsFrom: [{ excludedPromotionId: 2 }] },
    { id: 2, priority: 5, discountType: 'PERCENTAGE', discountValue: 20, exclusionsFrom: [] },
  ];
  // Promo 1 applied to line 1
  const appliedAfterLine1 = new Set<number>([1]);
  // Line 2: promo 2 is blocked (promo 1 excludes it); promo 1 is still available
  const line2Best = resolveBestPromotion(promos, 100, 1, appliedAfterLine1);
  expect(line2Best?.id).toBe(1); // promo 2 is excluded; promo 1 re-applies
});
```

